cs.NE, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV 

The paper introduces a new architecture for improving the performance of LSTM networks, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of stochastic memory operations, which falls under the category of probabilistic methods in machine learning, making cs.LG (Learning) a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper presents results on character level text prediction, which is a common NLP task, and could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
